Exceptions vs. Errors

Exception
 → Problem caused by or related to the program

Error
 → Problem outside of the program…
 → System-level issue
 → Something went wrong with the JVM

Important Syntax:
 try {}                                                → its like void in which it runs mainly
 catch {}                                              → if it catches an error this runs
 finally {}                                            → this always run mainly (This closes the exception handling)

HONORABLE MENTIONS:
    - Dividing any number with 0 as a double will return "Infinity"